{
  "stem": "10181.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 41.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when I got into the office, there must have been about 50, 60 kids there, one side, the girls, and one side, boys.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there was also a small room for the little babies.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "By the end of '43, there may have been 10, 15 left, aside from the Berenbaums themselves.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I'll tell you some-- you know, some of the things which went on in Westerbork.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "For instance, I think this was harassment by the commandant, you know.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The commandant, when Berenbaum used to haunt him every week, I think he got fed up with him, you know, so one week he decided that we had to go in quarantine because there was an outbreak of some disease.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I don't know what it was, what they claimed it was.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I think that they said it was probably polio or something like that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I don't think anybody was sick, so they put barbed wire around-- just around our-- our orphanage.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then people used to communicate through the barbed wire, so they used to put another barbed wire around the orphanage.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So we were really isolated.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I think this was more or less a form of-- of telling Berenbaum to lay off, you know, to-- to-- because he couldn't go out anymore.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We couldn't go out of the barracks.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We were just in there, and-- and-- but it wasn't like awful.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We couldn't move out, and he couldn't get out, either.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And he couldn't go out and-- and go to [INAUDIBLE] because he just couldn't go out and, you know, things like that.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And then we had a sort of distant relative who was a cousin of my father, I think she was.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Her name was Johanna Hamburger.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "That was her husband's name, Hamburger.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I think she might have been called Spiegel.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The German Jews who had been in the camp in 1939 didn't live in the big barracks like we did.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They had-- originally, they had like little apartments, small, but maybe one or two rooms.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then when it became the transit camp in-- it actually only became a transit camp in 1942, by the way.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, the Germans took it over.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were sort of squeezed a little bit, but they still had a little room of their own.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So it was easier to have parcels sent to-- to them than to the big barracks, and then she would bring them to us.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I remember.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I still see that picture, too, in front of my eyes where she would try to get the parcels to the orphanage when we were in isolation.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "She used to take a-- a long piece of wood, a flat piece of wood, put the parcel on the end of that piece of wood, and push the wood underneath both barbed wire fences to-- to-- to give us those-- those parcels.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "This was one of the things I remember, you know, and then I got sick.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I used to-- I had asthma, bronchitis.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I got-- I don't know.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I may have had a small case of measles.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I don't know what it was.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I got sick, where I had to go to the hospital and-- they thought-- because they thought I had-- there was an outbreak of scarlet fever, not in the orphanage, in the camp.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they thought that maybe I had scarlet fever, you know, so they took me to the hospital.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I remember Berenbaum coming at night and saying, how do you feel?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I said, oh, I feel OK.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He said, well, I want you to come out because I don't like to leave you here because if you stay here, if there's a transport, they're gonna take you, which they did.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, very often they took people from the hospital and put them on the transport.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Sometimes people thought being in the hospital would-- would save them, but it didn't.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, it depends on-- on what the program was for that week.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You know, one week, it may have saved you.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The next week, they may have decided we gonna take all the sick people, all the old people.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I remember they used to put the old people, infirm, on those carts and wheel them to the train, you know, to the work camp, back to the east.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So-- I-- I-- I think I left that same evening or next day.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He took me out, you know, because he was afraid that if I would stay there, you know, that I would disappear.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Mostly dry goods, you know, not bread.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You couldn't send bread, but bread we got.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Maybe cookies, marmalade, candies probably, yeah, I imagine.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
